==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sculptor
<hw>Sculp"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sculptor</ets>, fr. <ets>sculpere</ets>, <ets>sculptum</ets>, to
carve; cf. <ets>scalpere</ets> to cut, carve, scratch, and Gr. <?/ to
carve: cf. F. <ets>sculpteur</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
sculptures; one whose occupation is to carve statues, or works of
sculpture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, an artist who designs works of sculpture, his
first studies and his finished model being usually in a plastic
material, from which model the marble is cut, or the bronze is
cast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sculptress</ent>⟦br⟧
